Definition: characterized by often poignant difference or incongruity between what is expected and what actually is
Example: madness, an ironic fate for such a clear thinker; it was ironical that the well-planned scheme failed so completely
Synonyms: noun, communication, irony, attribute, ironical, characterized, by, often, poignant, difference, or, incongruity, between, what, is, expected, and, actually, madness, an, fate, for, such, a, clear, thinker, it, was, that, the, well-planned, scheme, failed, so, completely
Category: adj.all
